                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d752">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Choate</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hay states that Mr. Geldart says his shipment by the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Mashona</hi>, including necessary charges, would be covered by $1,000, and
                    that $575 would cover his shipment by the <hi rend="italic">Beatrice</hi>. If
                    better terms can not be had, however, he will accept the British offer.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
